Java dependencies → mvn install or gradle build
Node.js dependencies → npm install
Python dependencies → pip install
OS packages → yum install or apt-get install
------------------------------------------

Node.js
----------

FROM node:20-alpine

WORKDIR /app

COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm install

COPY . .

EXPOSE 3000

CMD ["npm", "start"]

--------
npm install

It installs all Node.js dependencies listed in your package.json file.

So if your package.json has:

{
  "dependencies": {
    "express": "^4.18.0",
    "mongoose": "^8.0.0"
  }
}

-------------------
Java (Spring Boot)
-------------

FROM eclipse-temurin:21-jre

WORKDIR /app

COPY target/app.jar app.jar

EXPOSE 8080

ENTRYPOINT ["java", "-jar", "app.jar"]

---------------------
Python
---------------

FROM python:3.12-slim

WORKDIR /app

COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install -r requirements.txt

COPY . .

CMD ["python", "app.py"]
------------------------------

installs Python libraries such as:

flask
requests
pandas
boto3

from requirements.txt.
